Package ohos.aafwk.ability.startsetting

Class AbilityStartSetting

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.aafwk.ability.startsetting.AbilityStartSetting

  • public class AbilityStartSetting
extends Object
    Defines special properties for an ability, which can be passed as an input parameter in the call when you start the ability.

    • Field Detail

      • BOUNDS_KEY

        public static final String BOUNDS_KEY
        Indicates the name of the ability window size property.

        This property takes effect when the Page ability is in ohos.aafwk.ability.AbilityWindowConfiguration.MULTI_WINDOW_DISPLAY_FLOATING mode. You are advised to set this property when starting a new mission.

        Since:
        4
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • WINDOW_DISPLAY_ID_KEY

        public static final String WINDOW_DISPLAY_ID_KEY
        Indicates the name of the display device ID property.

        This property is used for presenting the window display of an ability on another device, for example, projecting the window of an ability from the current device to a TV.

        Since:
        4
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • WINDOW_MODE_KEY

        public static final String WINDOW_MODE_KEY
        Indicates the name of the ability window display mode property.

        The window display mode of an ability can be any of the following values:

        • ohos.aafwk.ability.AbilityWindowConfiguration.MULTI_WINDOW_DISPLAY_FULLSCREEN
        • ohos.aafwk.ability.AbilityWindowConfiguration.MULTI_WINDOW_DISPLAY_PRIMARY
        • ohos.aafwk.ability.AbilityWindowConfiguration.MULTI_WINDOW_DISPLAY_SECONDARY
        • ohos.aafwk.ability.AbilityWindowConfiguration.MULTI_WINDOW_DISPLAY_FLOATING

        Since:
        4
        See Also:
